Ask HN: Imagine an AI trained on every word written or spoken by everyone
text:
I'm guessing China is developing such an AI right now. They have the means and the motivation to capture every written or spoken word of every Chinese citizen. Probably every TikToker too!

Presumably this all goes into a giant, up to the minute training data set.

I wonder what such an AI could be used for, any speculation?

Show HN: Random Aerial Airport Views
text:
Hi HN!

Sharing Random Airport

Inspired by RandomStreetView (which I find weirdly addictive), and a passion for air travel.

Probably not for everyone, but I hope some of you find it interesting!

Needless to say, open to feedback!

Enjoy clicking!

Further reading:

TECH: It's Build in React, NodeJS, with a Notion DB. The code is public on Github. It is spaghetti though ... Especially open to feedback here.

DB: The db is publicly available (and editable), I can add the link in comments if anyone would like to have a look .

KNOWN ISSUES: I would like to improve the design, pic loading performance and quality of (some) pics.

Ask HN: What Browser Instead of Firefox?
text:
I've been using Firefox since nearly 30 years, currently on Android and Windows.

For me it is a pain to use now. On Windows it force-updated and I've lost all plugins and the session with more than 50 tabs. On Android it crashes Android once a week and opens tabs with Urls as empty Windows regularily, sometimes after clicking on other tabs the tab is loaded, sometime I have to copy the URL and open another tab for the URL to load.

I'm on the breaking point and want something else. I'm waiting for Ladybird but it's not yet available and I don't want to use Chrome b/c Google.

Any suggestions?
